Deputy President William Ruto has asked the Kamba and Western Kenya leaders to play a leading role in marketing the Jubilee Party manifesto.Ruto said it is the responsibility of leaders to sell the party&rsquo;s manifesto at the grassroots. He addressed a delegation of leaders from Ukambani and Western who separately visited him at his Karen office in Nairobi yesterday. The Deputy President said the government has implemented most of its development agenda across the country. &ldquo;We are proud of our scorecard, and that is why we want to challenge our friends in the opposition to tell us what they did for Kenyans when they served for years in government,&rdquo; Ruto said. The Western Kenya delegation was led by Bungoma Governor Kenneth Lusaka and MPs Boniface Otsiula (Bumula), John Waluke (Sirisia), Bernard Shinali (Ikolomani) and Benjamin Washiali (Mumias East).Others were Reginalda Wanyonyi (Bungoma), Mary Emase (Teso South), Arthur Odera (Teso North), Malulu Injendi (Malava) and Emmanuel Wangwe (Navakholo). The Kamba delegation included MPs Victor Munyaka (Machakos Town) and Kisoi Munyao (Mbooni).